      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3, a definitive example of the E46 chassis. This specimen features the S54 3.2L inline-six, a naturally aspirated marvel equipped with individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing for a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is mechanically flawless, featuring a crisp 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock with zero lash. Critical maintenance has been proactively addressed, including rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral G-loads. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping and bushing elasticity, providing the precise turn-in and feedback expected of a showroom-quality M-car. A rare find for the collector seeking mechanical perfection.",
